docs.lead_paragraph: Business in the foreign exchange market last week continued to be dominated by the Holland guilder. However, some of the nervousness and tension of the preceding week had disappeared with the formation of another Colijn Cabinet, with the result that the guilder closed at an advance of 80 points, at 67.90 cents, compared with a loss of 93 points in the preceding week.

headline.main: FOREIGN EXCHANGE RATES; WEEK ENDED AUG. 3, 1935.

docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Aug. 13. -- Exports increased in June to all grand divisions except Asia and Northern North America, as compared with the same month last year, the Commerce Department reported today. Imports increased from all grand divisions except...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Aug. 13. -- Exports increased in June to all grand divisions except Asia and Northern North America, as compared with the same month last year, the Commerce Department reported today. Imports increased from all grand divisions except Asia.

headline.main: JUNE EXPORTS ROSE TO FIVE DIVISIONS; Only Asia and Canada Took Less Goods in Comparison With Last Year.
